lign: inherit;"><br></span></h2><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><span style="letter-spacing: 0px; text-align: inherit;">Emma </span><br></h2></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1677750491880" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1677750491880" style=""><lt-highlighter contenteditable="false" class="lt--mac-os" data-lt-linked="1" style="display: none; z-index: auto !important;"><lt-div spellcheck="false" class="lt-highlighter__wrapper" style="width: 765.328px !important; height: 44px !important; transform: none !important; transform-origin: 382.664px 22px !important; zoom: 1 !important;"><lt-div class="lt-highlighter__scroll-element" style="top: 0px !important; left: 0px !important; width: 765px !important; height: 53px !important;"></lt-div></lt-div></lt-highlighter><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc="" data-lt-tmp-id="lt-419339" spellcheck="false" data-gramm="false"><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><span style="letter-spacing: 0px; text-align: inherit;"><br></span></h2><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Sales Intern & Warehouse Team</h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1677751139628" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1677751139628"><lt-highlighter contenteditable="false" class="lt--mac-os" data-lt-linked="1" style="display: none; z-index: auto !important;"><lt-div spellcheck="false" class="lt-highlighter__wrapper" style="width: 765.328px !important; height: 644.844px !important; transform: none !important; transform-origin: 382.664px 322.422px !important; zoom: 1 !important;"><lt-div class="lt-highlighter__scroll-element" style="top: 0px !important; left: 0px !important; width: 765px !important; height: 644.844px !important;"><canvas class="lt-highlighter__canvas" width="14" height="20" style="display: none; top: 622px !important; left: 284px !important;"></canvas></lt-div></lt-div></lt-highlighter><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-justify-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc="" data-lt-tmp-id="lt-38138" spellcheck="false" data-gramm="false"><p style="font-size: 16px; font-family: &quot;Work Sans&quot;, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit !important;"><span style="color: rgb(61, 66, 70); caret-color: rgb(61, 66, 70); letter-spacing: 0px; background-color: var(--body_bg);"><br></span></p><p style="font-size: 16px; font-family: &quot;Work Sans&quot;, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit !important;"><span style="color: rgb(61, 66, 70); caret-color: rgb(61, 66, 70); letter-spacing: 0px; background-color: var(--body_bg);">Hey Everyone! I’m Emma, some of you readers might remember me from my '</span><span style="caret-color: rgb(61, 66, 70); letter-spacing: 0px; color: rgb(61, 66, 70); background-color: rgb(253, 235, 242);">What’s in your bag</span><span style="color: rgb(61, 66, 70); caret-color: rgb(61, 66, 70); letter-spacing: 0px; background-color: var(--body_bg);">?' segment and the '</span><span style="color: rgb(61, 66, 70); caret-color: rgb(61, 66, 70); letter-spacing: 0px; background-color: rgb(253, 235, 242);">Acne Routine Reel</span><span style="color: rgb(61, 66, 70); caret-color: rgb(61, 66, 70); letter-spacing: 0px; background-color: var(--body_bg);">' both on the KS Instagram. !</span></p><p style="color: rgb(61, 66, 70); font-size: 16px; font-family: &quot;Work Sans&quot;, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important;"><br></p><p style="color: rgb(61, 66, 70); font-size: 16px; font-family: &quot;Work Sans&quot;, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important;"><strong>Tell us about your roots!</strong></p><p style="font-size: 16px; font-family: &quot;Work Sans&quot;, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit !important;"><span style="color: rgb(61, 66, 70);">I was born in <span style="background-color: rgb(253, 235, 242);">Thailand</span> and moved to The Netherlands at the age of 6.  The Thailand culture is very close to my heart and I love going back for visits. I feel that my deep connection to my culture has also connected me with Asian beauty in general.&nbsp;</span></p><p style="font-size: 16px; font-family: &quot;Work Sans&quot;, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit !important;"><br></p><p style="font-size: 16px; font-family: &quot;Work Sans&quot;, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit !important;"><span style="caret-color: rgb(234, 0, 0); font-weight: bold;">Tell us about your experience with Korean skin care and KS!</span></p><p style="font-size: 16px; font-family: &quot;Work Sans&quot;, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit !important;"><span style="color: rgb(61, 66, 70);">Getting to work at KS has been such a fun experience, but also I’ve learned a lot. I enjoy finding out about new, upcoming brands and learning how certain skincare ingredients can target your skin’s concerns. This has helped me so much with finding <span style="background-color: rgb(253, 235, 242);">a better personal skin routine</span> and understanding which skincare products are most suitable for my skin type. I love seeing Korean skin care as a <span style="background-color: rgb(253, 235, 242);">beauty enhancer</span>, instead of something that completely changes your natural look.</span></p><p style="color: rgb(61, 66, 70); font-size: 16px; font-family: &quot;Work Sans&quot;, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important;"><br></p><p style="color: rgb(61, 66, 70); font-size: 16px; font-family: &quot;Work Sans&quot;, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">How do you describe the perfect day for you?</span></p><p style="font-size: 16px; font-family: &quot;Work Sans&quot;, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit !important;"><span style="color: rgb(61, 66, 70);">My perfect day is spending time with my <span style="background-color: rgb(253, 235, 242);">family</span> and making traditional Thai dishes. I also love spending time with my <span style="background-color: rgb(253, 235, 242);">friends</span>. Speaking of friends, I am a huge fan of FRIENDS and could binge-watch a season or two anytime. Anyone else currently catching up on the new season of YOU? I’m really enjoying the different location setting and new characters in this season and can’t wait to see how things play out. Other than binge-wacthing shows I really enjoy disco bowling and on days when I feel like I need to be more active I head to the gym.</span></p><p style="color: rgb(61, 66, 70); font-size: 16px; font-family: &quot;Work Sans&quot;, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important;"><br></p><p style="color: rgb(61, 66, 70); font-size: 16px; font-family: &quot;Work Sans&quot;, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important;"><b>Emma's favourite products:</b></p></div></div></div><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-4 gf_col-md-4 gf_col-xs-12 gf_col-sm-12" id="c-1677660872347" data-id="1677660872347"><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1677750396885" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1677750396885" data-resolution="3000x3000" style=""><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/53046889-2e11-4c60-9b4c-3ee8c19689d8/-/format/auto/-/preview/300